                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 New Delhi, Sept. 24 (PTI): Aamir Khans film Peepli Live has been selected as Indias official entry to next years Oscars in the Best Foreign Film category. Directed by Anusha Rizvi and shot in a village in Madhya Pradesh, the film depicts the growing rural-urban divide in India.          
	This is good news. I feel honoured and happy to be selected to represent my country. My congratulations to Anusha Rizvi and the entire team of Peepli Live, Aamir Khan said. This is his third film to be selected after Lagaan (2001) and Taare Zameen Par(2007).                  
	 Vadodara (PTI): Three persons were held after the discovery of six crude bombs near a religious place in Vadodara today, Gujarat police said. Each bomb weighed 1.1kg and was capable of causing damage within a radius of 5-10 metres. The trio were present near the place where the bombs were found and were being interrogated.                  
	 Amritsar (PTI): Raja Mohammed Ali, a childhood friend of Prime Minister Manmohan Singh, died after suffering a heart attack in Pakistan, family sources said. Ali was 78. Both had studied together in Chakwal in Pakistans Punjab province. Ali came to India in 2008 to meet Singh . The Prime Ministers Office has been informed about his death.                                                                                                                                              
